  • Method Details

    • throwIfNotOK

      protected final void throwIfNotOK(String operation, Enum<?> command) throws UnexpectedResponseCodeException
      Throw an exception if the response is not an OK.
      Parameters:
      operation - The overall operation that was being done.
      command - The particular command that this is a response to.
      Throws:
      UnexpectedResponseCodeException - If the response was a failure.
      UnroutableMessageException - If the response was specifically that the message couldn't be routed.
